YouTube accounts hacked by malware
text:
Search "Disable Windows Smart Screen, as well as update the Visual C++ package" "Disable/remove antivirus" on Google for an exact match of the hacked accounts, as well as some google sites, blog posts, and github repositories.

The hacked Youtube channels are all different, and the format slightly varies, but it's always has two things: First, a video showing a demonstration of the installation, and second, instructions to disable antivirus before installation.

Medium.com Competitor
text:
I have been using Medium for a while now and despite there being some quality posts (every now and then), the majority of the platform recommends you shitty articles. Not to mention that most of them are paywall gated.

I'm creating a Medium competitor website that would be free for everyone, and that would compensate writers through a split of ad revenue. The major differentiator is that it would have a recommendation engine that pushes out content that is hyper-personalized to you, similar to TikTok.

What do you guys think?
